 Makhanda - Eastern Cape SAPS Provincial Commissioner, Lt Gen Liziwe Ntshinga, on Monday condemned what police termed the 'callous and ruthless killing' of well-known artist, Ayanda Nondlwana, who was killed in the early hours of Sunday morning. “Our deepest condolences to the family, friends and fans of Ayanda, who was well-known in the artistic circle," she said. "The untimely death has sent shock waves through the local and international community. We have a assigned a seasoned detective to investigate this case." According to police spokesperson, Captain Mali Govender, in the early hours of Sunday, Nondlwana was in the company of a friend and looking for someone with a lighter to light up his cigarette. "He saw security guards and informed his friend that he will go and get a light from them. His friend continued to walk away," she said. "Nondlwana then walked off with the guards and his friend decided to follow him. "He was some distance away. A few minutes later he was informed from a passer-by that his friend was stabbed after an alleged argument." Nondlwana died at the scene. "Shortly after the incident, a male in his thirties handed himself over at the Grahamstown SAPS. He will appear in the local magistrate’s court on Tuesday." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 